on.dragenter:
(e, el, s) => {
          e.preventDefault()
          e.stopPropagation()
          if (!el.parent.data) return
          const isSame = el.parent.data.fromIndex === el.key
          const isSameGroup = el.parent.data.state === s.parent
          const isRootNode = e.target === el.node
          if (isSame || !isSameGroup || isRootNode) return
          el.parent.data.active = el.key
          el.setProps({
            transform: `scale(0.97)`,
            opacity: '0.9'
          })
        }
on.dragleave:
(e, el, s) => {
          e.preventDefault()
          e.stopPropagation()
          if (!el.parent.data) return
          const isSame = el.parent.data.fromIndex === el.key
          const isSameGroup = el.parent.data.state === s.parent
          const isRootNode = e.target === el.node
          if (isSame || !isSameGroup || isRootNode) return
          el.parent.data.active = el.key
          el.setProps({
            opacity: '1',
            transform: 'none'
          })
        }

p.text: Example code:

Functions allow you to write reusable frontend and backend functions and call them anytime during your flow. Functions can be used as lambda, self sustaining executable scripts and can be shared across your internal Symbols app or externally with integrations.

Frontend functions can be called within the browser when you want to execute some browser related functionality on your users browser. It can be perfectly used on events such as onClick, onLoad and etc. Most often frontend functions are used to reuse some functionality or wrap API requests in one place.

p.text: Backend functions are running on hosted custom node servers where you can write executable functions that runs on node.js environment. Most often they are used to create safe gateway with integrations where you safely store API keys and make requests to any other third party provider. Backend functions can be called within platform as they are built-in, or by REST API request from any other location.
You can set accessibility options such as Private or Public, as well as set CORS or JWT options to them.

Backend functions require server configuration that runs individual server for your function thats isolated and can handle a specific need to run custom logic. Symbols provides recommended defaults for most use, but you can customize configuration or set to auto scale options. Please be mindful that configuration affects on costs by traffic usage.
Using server functions might add additional cost when exceeding limits included in your current plan. Costs are calculated by usage and traffic and they follow:
